insurance premiums.
Second, there is a need for research on the development of more sophisticated security maturity models.
These models should consider not only technical cybersecurity capabilities but also organizational culture,
employee awareness, and governance mechanisms. Integrating these factors into the framework would
enable insurers to better assess an organization's overall cybersecurity readiness and tailor insurance
premiums accordingly.
Third, future research should explore the integration of emerging technologies, such as artificial intelligence and machine learning, into the socioeconomic modelling framework. These technologies can
enhance the accuracy and efficiency of risk assessment and pricing processes, enabling insurers to provide
more customized and cost-effective cyber-insurance policies.
Lastly, there is a need for empirical studies that validate the effectiveness of the proposed framework
in real-world settings. These studies should assess the framework's ability to accurately capture organizational structure, evaluate cybersecurity maturity, and determine appropriate insurance premiums. By
conducting such studies, researchers can validate the framework's effectiveness and identify potential
areas for improvement.

## Conclusion

In conclusion, the pricing of insurance for risks associated with information technology systems requires
a comprehensive modelling framework that integrates operations management, security, and economics.
The proposed socioeconomic modelling framework, which incorporates entity relationship diagrams,
security maturity models, and economic models, addresses the challenge of capturing organizational
structure in the design and pricing of cyber-insurance policies. However, further research is needed to
explore the specific factors influencing insurance pricing, develop sophisticated security maturity models,
integrate emerging technologies, and validate the effectiveness of the framework in real-world settings.
By addressing these knowledge gaps, researchers can contribute to the advancement of cyber-insurance
pricing and facilitate the development of more accurate and tailored insurance policies.

